<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>A suggestion then.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ceyana">Ceyana</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:52 p.m. 29/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> A suggestion then.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1767" TARGET=_self>For the Sake of Role Playing..</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>You know, none of this would be needed if an adequite faction system were implemented. All the servers could be PvP, it wouldn't matter. Loose faction for killing your own race, gain it for killing opposing races, be KOS by guards within the citys for a low faction... it would solve a hell of a lot of problems. You don't need seperate servers with different rules. Modify the system on all the servers to be the same, and you'll have a much better game in my oppinion. You could even make it so character below level 5 are non-PvP... it takes some time to get to level 5, and i'm sure most people won't completely ruin their hard work by killing same race characters and killing their faction after so many hours of play.

<P>Simplicity is best. That's the way I see it anyway. No need to be as complicated as it is. You're already splitting the EQ community with the current server structure, why not bring it together?
<P>- Ceyana
<P>&gt; I know I haven't been around alot. I have resigned as the PvP GM
<BR>&gt; of EQ. It did not allow me enough freedom to interact with the
<BR>&gt; community and my priority on PvP didn't quite mesh with other's
<BR>&gt; priorities. I am however happy to see it running well. I'm also
<BR>&gt; working extremely hard on redesigning the main everworld site..
<BR>&gt; (which is extremely hard when you're feeling not so creative). I
<BR>&gt; am still very much an advocate of PvP and will push petitions
<BR>&gt; for changes that the PvP community wants. I just had a thought
<BR>&gt; about the Limits on roleplaying because of the lack of PvP on
<BR>&gt; the non PvP servers. I'd almost like to see it set where if an
<BR>&gt; Ogre comes into a human newbie zone that he is attackable by any
<BR>&gt; humans in that zone, and can only attack if attacked. (He/She
<BR>&gt; knows what they're getting into by entering a zone less
<BR>&gt; accepting of their race) It would make raids on towns and events
<BR>&gt; alot easier where you don't have to be PvP to do it and it would
<BR>&gt; also buff roleplaying a bit. Ogres shouldn't be running around
<BR>&gt; freely among humans just outside the Qeynos gates. I know there
<BR>&gt; will be some access issues with this idea (means of travel
<BR>&gt; through zones) but none the less, it would be nice to see a tad
<BR>&gt; more realism to the race thing.
<P>&gt; Your thoughts?
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
